==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Apostolate
<hw>A*pos"to*late</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>apostolatus</ets>, fr. <ets>apostolus</ets>. See
<er>Apostle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The dignity, office, or
mission, of an apostle; apostleship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Judas had miscarried and lost his <qex>apostolate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The dignity or office of the pope, as the holder of
the apostolic see.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apostolical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Apostolic</ent>⟦br⟧
